Communication with Flex was good, and polite, Flex always responded pretty quickly, the linens were clean and fresh, sufficient towels and the apartment is well located. Nearby is a bus stop and also a subway station. Clean kitchen and clean bathroom, but in my opinion the apartment needs a little renovation (e.g. painting).
Check-in quickly, easily and independently. Because the apartment needs minor renovation (e.g. painting), Flex gets 4 stars from me, otherwise Flex would have gotten 5 stars. Thank you for the courtesy and hospitality.
Elijah Lugenn
Washington, DC
Rating 4 out of 5
, ·
4 days ago
We arrived at Istanbul Airport. We had a luxury van waiting to take us to the property. Flex was extremely responsive to our needs. They let us check in early.
The property is located in the same building as the Raddison Hotel, who also helped out to make it a more pleasurable experience.
The property mostly matched the photos. The property is in need of a little TLC and attention to detailed amenities, which I notified Flex about. I'm confident they will address the minor concerns in a proactive way.
The property is in a great location and convenient to anything you'd like to do in Istanbul. We took a 15 min taxi to the ferry for the Asian side. There are also things to see and do within a 10 min walk. Although we did not spend much time in the condo, it was nice to have this condo as a base to start from. The bed and couch were comfortable. We did not, however, use all the available items in the condo. We recommend you stay here and we look forward to staying here in the future
